#: ../../../topics/autothrottle.rst:3
msgid "AutoThrottle extension"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/autothrottle.rst:5
msgid ""
"This is an extension for automatically throttling crawling speed based on "
"load of both the Scrapy server and the website you are crawling."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/autothrottle.rst:9
msgid "Design goals"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/autothrottle.rst:11
msgid "be nicer to sites instead of using default download delay of zero"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/autothrottle.rst:12
msgid ""
"automatically adjust scrapy to the optimum crawling speed, so the user "
"doesn't have to tune the download delays and concurrent requests to find the "
"optimum one. the user only needs to specify the maximum concurrent requests "
"it allows, and the extension does the rest."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/autothrottle.rst:18
msgid "How it works"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/autothrottle.rst:20
msgid ""
"In Scrapy, the download latency is measured as the time elapsed between "
"establishing the TCP connection and receiving the HTTP headers."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/autothrottle.rst:23
msgid ""
"Note that these latencies are very hard to measure accurately in a "
"cooperative multitasking environment because Scrapy may be busy processing a "
"spider callback, for example, and unable to attend downloads. However, these "
"latencies should still give a reasonable estimate of how busy Scrapy (and "
"ultimately, the server) is, and this extension builds on that premise."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/autothrottle.rst:32
msgid "Throttling algorithm"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/autothrottle.rst:34
msgid ""
"This adjusts download delays and concurrency based on the following rules:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/autothrottle.rst:36
msgid ""
"spiders always start with one concurrent request and a download delay of :"
"setting:`AUTOTHROTTLE_START_DELAY`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/autothrottle.rst:38
msgid ""
"when a response is received, the download delay is adjusted to the average "
"of previous download delay and the latency of the response."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/autothrottle.rst:41
msgid ""
"The AutoThrottle extension honours the standard Scrapy settings for "
"concurrency and delay. This means that it will never set a download delay "
"lower than :setting:`DOWNLOAD_DELAY` or a concurrency higher than :setting:"
"`CONCURRENT_REQUESTS_PER_DOMAIN` (or :setting:`CONCURRENT_REQUESTS_PER_IP`, "
"depending on which one you use)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/autothrottle.rst:48
msgid "Settings"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/autothrottle.rst:50
msgid "The settings used to control the AutoThrottle extension are:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/autothrottle.rst:52
msgid ":setting:`AUTOTHROTTLE_ENABLED`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/autothrottle.rst:53
msgid ":setting:`AUTOTHROTTLE_START_DELAY`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/autothrottle.rst:54
msgid ":setting:`AUTOTHROTTLE_MAX_DELAY`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/autothrottle.rst:55
msgid ":setting:`AUTOTHROTTLE_DEBUG`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/autothrottle.rst:56
msgid ":setting:`CONCURRENT_REQUESTS_PER_DOMAIN`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/autothrottle.rst:57
msgid ":setting:`CONCURRENT_REQUESTS_PER_IP`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/autothrottle.rst:58
msgid ":setting:`DOWNLOAD_DELAY`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/autothrottle.rst:60
msgid "For more information see :ref:`autothrottle-algorithm`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/autothrottle.rst:65
msgid "AUTOTHROTTLE_ENABLED"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/autothrottle.rst:67 ../../../topics/autothrottle.rst:94
msgid "Default: ``False``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/autothrottle.rst:69
msgid "Enables the AutoThrottle extension."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/autothrottle.rst:74
msgid "AUTOTHROTTLE_START_DELAY"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/autothrottle.rst:76
msgid "Default: ``5.0``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/autothrottle.rst:78
msgid "The initial download delay (in seconds)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/autothrottle.rst:83
msgid "AUTOTHROTTLE_MAX_DELAY"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/autothrottle.rst:85
msgid "Default: ``60.0``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/autothrottle.rst:87
msgid ""
"The maximum download delay (in seconds) to be set in case of high latencies."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/autothrottle.rst:92
msgid "AUTOTHROTTLE_DEBUG"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/autothrottle.rst:96
msgid ""
"Enable AutoThrottle debug mode which will display stats on every response "
"received, so you can see how the throttling parameters are being adjusted in "
"real time."
msgstr ""
